It sounds like you want to create a clickable image that, when clicked, reveals a dropdown menu with options like "delete" and "rename". In JavaScript, you can achieve this using event listeners and HTML elements.

Here's a possible approach:

1. Create an HTML structure for your image and dropdown menu:
```html
<div class="chat-info">
  <img src="your-image-url" alt="Chat Info">
  <ul class="dropdown-menu" style="display: none;">
    <li><a href="#">Delete</a></li>
    <li><a href="#">Rename</a></li>
  </ul>
</div>
```
2. Add a JavaScript event listener to the image element:
```javascript
const chatInfoImg = document.querySelector('.chat-info img');
chatInfoImg.addEventListener('click', function() {
  const dropdownMenu = this.nextElementSibling;
  dropdownMenu.style.display = 'block'; // show the dropdown menu
});
```
This code selects the image element, adds a click event listener, and when clicked, it finds the next sibling element (the dropdown menu) and sets its display property to 'block', making it visible.

3. To hide the dropdown menu when clicked outside, you can add an event listener to the document:
```javascript
document.addEventListener('click', function(event) {
  if (!event.target.closest('.chat-info')) {
    const dropdownMenus = document.querySelectorAll('.dropdown-menu');
    dropdownMenus.forEach((menu) => menu.style.display = 'none');
  }
});
```
This code listens for clicks on the document, and if the target element is not within the `.chat-info` container, it hides all dropdown menus.

